We came up with this hot-weather refresher to help deal with this summer’s glorious glut of English strawberries. Serves 4 150ml white rum – we use Cabby’s, which is made locally to us in east London4 tbsp lime juice400g strawberries, hulled and halved, plus 1 extra strawberry, sliced, to garnish 20 ice cubes Put everything into a powerful blender or NutriBullet and blend smooth. Pour into four chilled coupe or daiquiri glasses, garnish with slices of strawberry and serve. • Nick Gilkinson, Townsend at the Whitechapel Gallery, London E1